{
  "text": "http://ajp.psychiatryonline.org polar spectrum illness. In each pedigree the pattern of inheritance of mood disorder was consistent with a major gene model. This is certainly not the usual pattern of inheritance of bipolar disorder [CITATION_1] , and therefore it is important to clarify explicitly the assumptions that underpin the approach we took. We assumed that in each pedigree, a variant exists that acts as a highly penetrant autosomal dominant mutation and that the pathogenic variant(s) (which might be different in the two pedigrees) is rare because otherwise such pedigrees would be common in the population.",
